headline: Pharma’s new boomtown? Why drugmakers are setting up shop in a small Swiss city.
summary: While the EU and UK attempt to lure scientists with new financial incentives, Basel’s stable economy and emphasis on science remains a draw.

headline: Health Officials Hunt for Cases Connecting Covid Shot and Harm in Pregnant Women
summary: Top health officials under Robert F. Kennedy Jr. are compiling examples of harmful effects of Covid shots on pregnant women to share with the public, furthering the administration’s scrutiny of vaccines.
